cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SI

This paper proposes a novel method that combines graph neural networks and reinforcement learning to predict chemical reaction products. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper involves natural language processing. Additionally, since the paper uses graph representations, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible sub-categories.
